## Top Bridal Makeup Trends We're Loving in 2026

Bridal beauty has evolved beautifully this year, and Fort Lauderdale brides are embracing some stunning trends. Here's what we're seeing most in our studio right now:

### ✨ Luminous Skin, Always
The "no-makeup makeup" movement isn't going anywhere — it's evolving. In 2026, brides are asking for skin that looks *breathtaking*, not just covered. Think strategic highlighting, blurred pores, and a natural glow that photographs like a dream.

### 💋 Statement Lips Are Back
After years of neutral lips dominating bridal aesthetics, the bold lip is making a serious comeback. Deep berries, classic reds, and rich mauves are showing up at weddings everywhere — paired with softer, more understated eye looks to keep the balance right.

### 🌿 Botanical-Inspired Details
Pressed flower liner, delicate leaf motifs at the outer corner of the eye, and soft earthy tones inspired by nature are trending heavily — especially for garden weddings and outdoor ceremonies along Fort Lauderdale's waterfront venues.

### 👁️ Floating Liner & Graphic Eyes
For the fashion-forward bride, graphic liner — floated above the crease or used to create architectural shapes — is a bold, editorial choice that photographs spectacularly.

### 🌊 Sun-Kissed Bridal Glow
Because you're in South Florida, and it would be a crime not to. A beautifully blended bronzed glow, warm blush, and a hint of freckle-friendly coverage gives beach brides the perfect laid-back luxe look.

