## How to Prepare Your Skin for Your Wedding Day

Great makeup starts with great skin. Here's our pre-wedding skincare timeline:

**6 Months Out:**
Begin working with a dermatologist or licensed esthetician. Address any ongoing concerns — hyperpigmentation, acne, dryness — with plenty of time to see results and avoid any adverse reactions close to the wedding.

**3 Months Out:**
Establish a consistent routine: cleanser, moisturizer, SPF every morning, and a gentle retinol or vitamin C serum at night. Consistency is everything.

**4 Weeks Out:**
Schedule your last facial. Nothing too aggressive — a hydrating or brightening treatment is ideal. **Avoid** any new or experimental treatments this close to your wedding date.

**1 Week Out:**
Focus on hydration — inside and out. Drink plenty of water, reduce sodium and alcohol intake, and keep your skincare routine simple and gentle. Don't introduce any new products.

**The Night Before:**
Double-cleanse, apply a nourishing face mask, and moisturize generously. Get your sleep. Seriously — no concealer in the world replaces eight hours of rest.

**Morning Of:**
Cleanse gently, moisturize, and apply your SPF. Then leave your skin alone and let us work our magic.

